00:08:33,899 --> 00:08:36,633
<b>In exchange, Ethiopia agreed to an</b>

240
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:39,033
<b>in-depth assessment towards recognition.</b>

241
00:08:39,666 --> 00:08:42,466
<b>Not a guarantee, but the clearest signal</b>

242
00:08:42,466 --> 00:08:44,300
<b>yet from a major African power.</b>

243
00:08:44,699 --> 00:08:46,366
<b>Then, Israel went further.</b>

244
00:08:47,133 --> 00:08:49,766
<b>Prime Minister Netanyahu announced a full</b>

245
00:08:49,766 --> 00:08:50,800
<b>diplomatic recognition,</b>

246
00:08:51,366 --> 00:08:53,533
<b>including the exchange of ambassadors and</b>

247
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,633
<b>the opening of embassies.</b>

248
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:57,666
<b>Israel, the first UN member to formally</b>

249
00:08:57,666 --> 00:09:00,166
<b>recognize Somaliland in 34 years.</b>

250
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,366
<b>Somalia called it an</b>

251
00:09:02,366 --> 00:09:03,566
<b>attack on sovereignty.</b>

252
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:06,466
<b>Within hours, the African Union responded</b>

253
00:09:06,466 --> 00:09:08,533
<b>by firmly rejecting</b>

254
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,233
<b>any initiative aimed at</b>

255
00:09:10,233 --> 00:09:11,500
<b>recognizing Somaliland.</b>

256
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:14,166
<b>The same union that called the case</b>

257
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:16,300
<b>"unique" and "self-justified"</b>

258
00:09:16,699 --> 00:09:17,966
<b>now calls recognition</b>

259
00:09:17,966 --> 00:09:19,600
<b>a dangerous precedent.</b>

260
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,033
<b>So what's happening here?</b>

261
00:09:22,966 --> 00:09:23,933
<b>Somaliland isn't trying</b>

262
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:25,100
<b>to become independent.</b>

263
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:27,800
<b>They're arguing they already were.</b>

264
00:09:28,066 --> 00:09:29,699
<b>For five days in 1960,</b>

265
00:09:30,366 --> 00:09:31,866
<b>recognized by 35 nations,</b>

266
00:09:32,366 --> 00:09:33,433
<b>before a union that was</b>

267
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:34,866
<b>never properly ratified,</b>

268
00:09:35,266 --> 00:09:36,733
<b>the documents support this.</b>

269
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,033
<b>The 1963 ruling supports this.</b>

270
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,566
<b>The African Union's own investigation</b>

271
00:09:41,566 --> 00:09:43,933
<b>called it "unique" and "self-justified".</b>

272
00:09:44,766 --> 00:09:47,466
<b>That first narrative, Somaliland is just</b>

273
00:09:47,466 --> 00:09:50,133
<b>a separatist region with no legal basis.</b>

274
00:09:50,899 --> 00:09:53,199
<b>The 1960 independence, the 35</b>

275
00:09:53,199 --> 00:09:55,533
<b>recognitions, the Never-Ratified Treaty,</b>

276
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,733
<b>the 2005 report, that under a concept.</b>

277
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:02,133
<b>But the second narrative, Somaliland was</b>

278
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:03,166
<b>never part of Somalia.</b>

279
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:06,166
<b>The 31 years of practice, the</b>

280
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:07,000
<b>international recognition,</b>

281
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:08,366
<b>and the voluntary</b>

282
00:10:08,366 --> 00:10:11,066
<b>merger, that complicates it.</b>

283
00:10:11,466 --> 00:10:12,766
<b>The legal case is stronger</b>

284
00:10:12,766 --> 00:10:14,233
<b>than most people realize.</b>

285
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:16,733
<b>The political obstacles are real.</b>

286
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:19,166
<b>The African Union fears that recognition</b>

287
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:21,366
<b>would spur more secessionist cases.</b>

288
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:23,733
<b>South Sudan is the only</b>

289
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,033
<b>modern African secession.</b>

290
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:27,966
<b>And that required parent-state consent.</b>

291
00:10:29,366 --> 00:10:30,966
<b>Somalia will never consent.</b>

292
00:10:31,966 --> 00:10:32,500
<b>Which means the</b>

293
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:33,966
<b>international community has to decide.</b>

294
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:36,166
<b>Does documentary evidence</b>

295
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:37,866
<b>trump political convenience?</b>

296
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:40,399
<b>Somaliland is not merely de facto.</b>

297
00:10:40,966 --> 00:10:43,333
<b>It is de jure by virtue of its</b>

298
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,833
<b>independence on June 26, 1960.</b>

299
00:10:46,066 --> 00:10:46,699
<b>The failure to</b>

300
00:10:46,699 --> 00:10:48,133
<b>acknowledge this is not ambiguity.</b>

301
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,133
<b>It is a political choice.</b>

302
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,033
<b>Israel just made that</b>

303
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,566
<b>choice impossible to ignore.</b>

304
00:10:54,466 --> 00:10:55,566
<b>The documents exist.</b>

305
00:10:56,166 --> 00:10:57,266
<b>The precedents exist.</b>

306
00:10:57,733 --> 00:10:59,966
<b>The AU's own investigation called it</b>

307
00:10:59,966 --> 00:11:01,333
<b>"unique" and "self-justified".</b>

308
00:11:02,166 --> 00:11:03,666
<b>The only thing missing is the</b>

309
00:11:03,666 --> 00:11:05,166
<b>political will to read them.</b>

310
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:07,266
<b>If you want to understand how colonial</b>

311
00:11:07,266 --> 00:11:08,800
<b>decisions still shape modern</b>

312
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,166
<b>conflicts, please subscribe.</b>

